The course is for those majoring in English Language and Literature and aims at providing the students with the knowledge and skills they need in order to write their BA theses in English.The students refresh and deepen their knowledge about the conventions of Anglo-American academic writing, read and analyse critically different types of academic texts and complete a variety of writing assignments. The focus is on analysing and improving their own and other students' written texts and, in the process, developing their cooperation skills.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at providing students of English Language and Literature with the knowledge and skills needed for writing BA theses in English, among them the ability to critically analyse their own and the other students' written texts and successfully manage their writing process.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of the course, the student will - know the key stages in the research cycle, develop their research plan and follow it; - find sources (including Internet sources) suitable for their research, analyse them critically and integrate them into their writing appropriately avoiding plagiarism; - be aware of their strengths and weaknesses in academic writing and able to find additional sources for developing their writing skills; - present academic papers orally and answer questions on them - analyse and evaluate academic texts and presentations by the other students bearing in mind the Anglo-American writing conventions and provide constructive feedback on them.
